 Asterisk Call Routing Stability & SIP Contact Management
Project focused on diagnosing and resolving call routing inconsistency in an Asterisk PBX environment using standard SIP principles.
Scope:

Troubleshooting inbound call delivery issues
SIP contact analysis and endpoint resolution
Configuration hardening (PJSIP AOR management)
CLI-based validation and testing

Key Activities:

Identified multiple active SIP contacts causing non-deterministic routing behavior
Implemented single-contact enforcement using standard Asterisk configuration
Validated call routing using CLI originate and channel state verification
Confirmed stable inbound and outbound call behavior
Developed a health check script to validate system state
Created backup and recovery procedure for configuration resilience

Outcome:

Deterministic call routing behavior
Stable endpoint reachability
Repeatable validation process
Improved operational reliability
